Teachers in public primary and secondary schools in Bayelsa State failed to turn up for classes for the new academic session even as schools formally resume on Monday.  Public primary and secondary schools in Bayelsa State are yet to resume for the 2016/2017 session because of the failure of the state government to settle the seven months salary arrears of teachers. October 3, 2016 In "News" Public primary and secondary schools in Bayelsa have yet to resume for the 2016/2017 session because of the failure of the state government to settle their seven months salary arrears. October 3, 2016 In "News" Public primary and secondary schools in Bayelsa have yet to resume for the 2016/2017 session because of the failure of the state government to settle their seven months salary arrears. October 3, 2016 In "News"